{"TopicId":96481,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Infiniglider Construction","CreatedByName":"Engineer of Stuff","CreatedById":106757,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-12T19:10:25Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Engineer of Stuff","CreatedById":106757,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-12T19:10:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWhat are the best ways to build an infiniglider? I tried to make one, but failed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAny tips?\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-01-13T19:47:55Z\u0022 title=\u002201/13/2015 07:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 13, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by Engineer Of Stuff\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anquietas314","CreatedById":8761,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-12T19:53:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EMake it light, put \u003Cstrong\u003Eloads\u003C/strong\u003E of control surfaces on it. Winglets (the controllable kind) and canards are especially good. There\u0027s really not much else to it tbh. A parachute (and engineer) might be a good idea if you expect to be able to land in one piece though \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOne of the more effective designs (for speed, at least):\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://www.skyrender.net/lp2/ksp/infiniglider2.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022infiniglider2.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYou don\u0027t really need that many control surfaces to make one fly though. It\u0027s perfectly possible to make ones that look somewhat similar to real planes \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-01-12T20:00:12Z\u0022 title=\u002201/12/2015 08:00  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 12, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by armagheddonsgw\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}